{"_id":"965edeaa-2432-31a3-9a3d-715ecd8d6791","authorName":"Patrick Kursawe","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"b20148f6b8a869f4b4264f299bed2c05","message":"Just ran into this problem again. I am using a SingleThreadScheduler to run things for a third party component on a dedicated STA thread, and I had a deadlock when trying to Dispose an object. Checked with ILSpy and saw a series of Task.Factory.StartNew without an explicit scheduler specification. So the single thread scheduler was used, and voila! we had the very classic deadlock. Thank you very much for this article!","postId":"2013_08_startnew-is-dangerous-4c5e3290-63e6-3320-85d1-3054cbca80ce","replyTo":"","date":"2018-03-12T13:50:45Z","timestamp":1520862645,"authorUserId":"disqus:patrickkursawe"}